1
00:00:18,839 --> 00:00:22,300
ANDREl RUBLEV

2
00:02:25,830 --> 00:02:27,530
Pull the rope.

3
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,539
This is one?

4
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,539
Arkhip, give me the strap.

5
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,539
Hold it.

6
00:02:42,849 --> 00:02:43,669
Take it.

7
00:02:44,849 --> 00:02:46,550
Look!

8
00:02:46,849 --> 00:02:48,550
lt's Yefim, isn't it?

9
00:03:09,810 --> 00:03:12,389
Come here and help.

10
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:13,629
Pull the rope.

11
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:15,520
Hold on a second.

12
00:03:15,819 --> 00:03:17,520
Come on, quick!

13
00:03:17,819 --> 00:03:19,520
Where is it?

14
00:03:20,819 --> 00:03:21,639
Here.

15
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:26,530
Come on, fast.

16
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:31,530
Lift it.

17
00:03:51,849 --> 00:03:54,370
-Lord. Let it go right.
-Untie it now.

18
00:03:59,789 --> 00:04:01,490
The rope is tangled.

19
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,500
Hold it!

20
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,500
We won't have enough time.

21
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,379
l'm ready!

22
00:04:11,810 --> 00:04:13,509
Archipushka! You try to
hold them!

23
00:04:13,810 --> 00:04:16,389
Just a second.

24
00:04:16,810 --> 00:04:18,509
Come on!

25
00:04:21,819 --> 00:04:24,399
Hold him, hold him!

26
00:04:36,829 --> 00:04:39,410
l'm here. l'm here.

27
00:04:42,839 --> 00:04:43,660
Cut the rope, man!

28
00:04:45,839 --> 00:04:48,420
Cut the rope!

29
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:51,420
l'll show you, cut the rope!

30
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,500
My God!

31
00:05:17,810 --> 00:05:19,509
Yefim!

32
00:05:19,810 --> 00:05:21,509
Where are you going?

33
00:05:21,810 --> 00:05:23,509
Archipushka!

34
00:05:25,810 --> 00:05:28,389
l'm flying! l'm flying!

35
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:56,360
Hey! Chase me! Chase me!

36
00:06:33,819 --> 00:06:36,399
My God! What is it?

37
00:06:57,769 --> 00:07:00,350
Archipushka!

38
00:08:00,769 --> 00:08:05,990
THE JESTER
Summer 140O

39
00:08:20,790 --> 00:08:21,610
Danil!

40
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,379
Danil! The father told you
to go back!

41
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:35,379
There is no one to paint
the icons.

42
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,500
For God's sake!

43
00:08:37,809 --> 00:08:39,509
lt's no business of yours.

44
00:08:39,809 --> 00:08:44,149
You will be sorry for that. You will
come begging on your knee's.

45
00:08:44,809 --> 00:08:46,509
Come on. You never know.

46
00:08:46,809 --> 00:08:48,509
We shall see.

47
00:08:53,789 --> 00:08:55,460
lt's not good.

48
00:08:55,759 --> 00:08:57,460
What?

49
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:59,460
That we are leaving Troitsa.

50
00:09:09,769 --> 00:09:11,470
lt's a shame.

51
00:09:13,769 --> 00:09:18,110
Aren't there enough painters in
Moscow without us, Danil?

52
00:09:18,779 --> 00:09:21,360
We'll find some sort of work.

53
00:09:21,779 --> 00:09:24,360
All this is right, but it's
a pity that...

54
00:09:24,789 --> 00:09:28,250
l passed this birch every day
and never noticed it.

55
00:09:28,789 --> 00:09:33,129
When you know you'll never see
it, again means something.

56
00:09:33,789 --> 00:09:37,250
lt's been ten years. Nine for
you, but ten for me.

57
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:40,379
No, seven for me
nine for you.

58
00:09:42,799 --> 00:09:44,500
-lt's raining.
-Come on here.

59
00:09:44,809 --> 00:09:46,509
Let's go. We will not melt.

60
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:28,309
The jesters were walking. Drunk
on mead and beer...

61
00:10:28,850 --> 00:10:31,429
when they met their master,
the Boyar...

62
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:33,549
and they sang, to greet him:

63
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,559
O master. O Boyar...

64
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:40,440
everything is ready in
the kitchen!

65
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:44,320
The Boyar's plump wife
is a choosy trollop.

66
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:52,210
Mistress, open the door.
The master's coming!

67
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:58,149
The Boyar yells: ''Jesters are all
thieves and drunkards!''

68
00:10:58,809 --> 00:11:02,269
''You should be whipped from
Friday to Friday!''

69
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:06,279
''You goats and tramps, drown
in your beer!''

70
00:11:07,820 --> 00:11:10,399
''Soon you will be impaled!''

71
00:11:10,830 --> 00:11:15,169
The Jesters grabbed him between
his navel and his knees.

72
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:22,169
They shaved his beard; what's a
Boyar without his beard?

73
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:27,299
Any woman would rather
he had a beard.

74
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:31,299
The Boyar yells, hops
about like a flea.

75
00:11:33,850 --> 00:11:37,309
He scurries home, raps
on the window.

76
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:45,200
But his wife doesn't recognize
his naked cheeks...

77
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:49,440
with no beard to grab hold of.

78
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:52,440
She whacked him with
a rolling pin.

79
00:11:53,830 --> 00:11:56,379
What a disgrace!

80
00:11:58,809 --> 00:12:02,269
''Cover your naked cheeks
with your breeches.''

81
00:12:03,809 --> 00:12:05,509
''Clear off, beardless Boyar!''

82
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:11,399
He hobbled off, pursued
by geese...

83
00:12:11,820 --> 00:12:14,399
and meet a priest...

84
00:12:15,820 --> 00:12:21,039
who mistook him for a woman and
dragged him into the bushes.

85
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:28,169
Without breeches...
he looks the same at each end.

86
00:12:59,799 --> 00:13:02,379
The woman saw a naked head...

87
00:13:02,799 --> 00:13:05,379
and grabbed it by the beard.

88
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:21,399
May we shelter from the storm?

89
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:22,639
Come in.

90
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:33,289
Do you want some beer?
You are soaking wet.

91
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:35,529
Thank you, we don't imbibe.

92
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,539
And don't play around with women.

93
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:40,289
God sent priests, but the
devil sent jesters.

94
00:16:18,799 --> 00:16:20,500
The woman saw a head!

95
00:16:22,799 --> 00:16:25,379
By the beard!

96
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:43,279
My woman might have been
playing in the bushes.

97
00:16:50,830 --> 00:16:52,529
l'll show you!

98
00:18:07,769 --> 00:18:10,349
Come here, you.

99
00:18:39,809 --> 00:18:41,509
What are you doing?

100
00:19:16,779 --> 00:19:18,480
Give it back to him.

101
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:37,500
Where were you, Kirill?

102
00:19:38,799 --> 00:19:40,500
Outside. Shall we go?

103
00:19:51,809 --> 00:19:55,269
Danil, the rain's stopped;
Iet's go.

104
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:27,430
Christ be with you, mistress.

105
00:21:24,839 --> 00:21:30,930
THEOPHANES THE GREEK
Summer-Winter-Spring-Summer-1405-1406

106
00:21:40,849 --> 00:21:42,549
l'm innocent!

107
00:21:52,869 --> 00:21:54,509
Let me go!

108
00:22:28,839 --> 00:22:30,539
ls anyone in here?

109
00:23:07,809 --> 00:23:09,509
Have you come to look?

110
00:23:10,809 --> 00:23:12,509
Yes, to look.

111
00:23:20,819 --> 00:23:23,400
Then look. We'll soon be finished.

112
00:23:25,829 --> 00:23:29,289
So you are Theophanes the Greek?

113
00:23:32,829 --> 00:23:35,410
Why look at me? Look there.

114
00:23:37,839 --> 00:23:39,539
Where are you from?

115
00:23:39,839 --> 00:23:42,420
From Andronnikov Monastery.

116
00:23:42,839 --> 00:23:46,299
From Andronnikov Monastery? Are you
by chance Andrei Rublev?

117
00:23:49,849 --> 00:23:50,670
No.

118
00:23:51,849 --> 00:23:55,250
l've heard everyone praise
this Rublev.

119
00:23:57,789 --> 00:24:01,250
He's good, but not as good as this.

120
00:24:04,799 --> 00:24:07,380
Such delicate colors.

121
00:24:11,809 --> 00:24:13,509
Oh Lord, it's just...

122
00:24:23,819 --> 00:24:27,279
Why did you stop praising me?
Go on.

123
00:24:27,819 --> 00:24:31,279
l can't. l can't find the
right words.

124
00:24:31,829 --> 00:24:35,289
Konstantin Kostechevsky was
right when he said:

125
00:24:35,829 --> 00:24:38,410
''Only with true insight...

126
00:24:38,829 --> 00:24:41,410
can you grasp its essence.''

127
00:24:43,839 --> 00:24:47,299
Whereas Andrei... and l'll
tell him to his face...

128
00:24:47,839 --> 00:24:50,420
He's like my brother.

129
00:24:54,779 --> 00:25:00,869
He's praised, it's true: he paints
well. With subtlety.

130
00:25:02,789 --> 00:25:05,369
But there's something Lacking
in all his work.

131
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:13,259
There's no awe, no faith...

132
00:25:13,799 --> 00:25:16,380
no faith that comes from the
depths of his soul.

133
00:25:18,809 --> 00:25:20,509
No simplicity.

134
00:25:21,809 --> 00:25:26,150
As Epiphanius said in ''The Life of
Saint Sergeius'':

135
00:25:26,809 --> 00:25:29,390
''Simplicity, without gaudiness.''

136
00:25:32,819 --> 00:25:35,400
That is what this is. It's sacred.

137
00:25:36,819 --> 00:25:41,160
Simplicity, without gaudiness...
you can't say it better.

138
00:25:41,829 --> 00:25:43,529
l see you are a wise man.

139
00:25:43,829 --> 00:25:45,529
lf so, is that a good thing?

140
00:25:45,829 --> 00:25:50,170
lf one is ignorant, isn't it better
to be guided by one's heart?

141
00:25:51,839 --> 00:25:55,240
ln much wisdom there
is much grief...

142
00:25:55,779 --> 00:25:59,240
And he who increases knowledge
increases sorrow.

143
00:26:06,789 --> 00:26:09,369
Proshka! Where is that oil?

144
00:26:10,789 --> 00:26:12,490
Whose ears should l box?

145
00:26:12,789 --> 00:26:14,490
lt is as though the earth has
swallowed everyone.

146
00:26:14,789 --> 00:26:17,369
They say you paint quickly.

147
00:26:17,799 --> 00:26:20,380
l cannot work any other way.
l got bored.

148
00:26:20,799 --> 00:26:24,259
l wasted a week on an icon once.

149
00:26:24,799 --> 00:26:26,500
You threw it away?

150
00:26:26,809 --> 00:26:28,509
No. l used the board to
press cabbage.

151
00:26:29,809 --> 00:26:32,390
lt's all so boring.

152
00:26:32,809 --> 00:26:34,509
l have pupils and assistants
in abundance...

153
00:26:34,809 --> 00:26:36,509
But none of them is any good.

154
00:26:36,819 --> 00:26:38,519
They can neither red nor write.

155
00:26:41,819 --> 00:26:44,400
Listen, help me. Be my assistant.

156
00:26:47,829 --> 00:26:49,529
Don't make fun of me.

157
00:26:49,829 --> 00:26:51,529
l'm not making fun of you.

158
00:26:51,829 --> 00:26:54,349
ln spring, l must paint the Church of
the Annunciation in Moscow...

159
00:26:54,769 --> 00:26:57,349
and l have no assistants
to do it with.

160
00:26:57,769 --> 00:26:59,470
The scaffolding is being built.

161
00:26:59,769 --> 00:27:01,470
-Do you understand?
-l do understand.

162
00:27:01,779 --> 00:27:02,599
But l wouldn't be able to cope.

163
00:27:02,779 --> 00:27:04,480
l'll teach you. You never prepared
a wall for a fresco?

164
00:27:04,779 --> 00:27:09,119
You've a brain; even these idiots
can prepare a wall.

165
00:27:09,779 --> 00:27:14,119
l said no and l mean no.

166
00:27:14,789 --> 00:27:17,369
You know best...

167
00:27:17,789 --> 00:27:19,490
But mind you don't regret;
l am rancorous.

168
00:27:19,789 --> 00:27:24,130
l may regret it, but it's
a sin for you.

169
00:27:24,799 --> 00:27:28,259
An unknown monk comes to you...

170
00:27:28,799 --> 00:27:31,380
and you like the fact that you can
talk about books with him...

171
00:27:31,809 --> 00:27:35,269
and you decide to take him
and favor him.

172
00:27:35,809 --> 00:27:38,390
But l haven't looked at a book for
three years and l don't want to.

173
00:27:38,809 --> 00:27:41,390
-Why?
-l have a different road.

174
00:27:42,819 --> 00:27:44,519
Wicked bastards!

175
00:27:44,819 --> 00:27:46,519
Where is Proshka?
Where is Vikenty?

176
00:27:46,819 --> 00:27:49,400
They ran to the square to see how
they were going to kill the ruler.

177
00:27:50,819 --> 00:27:55,099
Wicked bastards!

178
00:27:55,759 --> 00:27:57,460
See?

179
00:28:08,779 --> 00:28:10,480
And you don't want to help?

180
00:28:11,779 --> 00:28:13,480
-l shall die soon.
-You shouldn't say that.

181
00:28:25,789 --> 00:28:28,369
The other night l dreamed
of an angel.

182
00:28:29,799 --> 00:28:33,259
He said: ''Come with me.''

183
00:28:33,799 --> 00:28:35,500
l said: ''l shall die soon
without you.''

184
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:40,259
You won't change your mind,
will you?

185
00:28:53,789 --> 00:28:56,339
Only on one condition.

186
00:29:00,759 --> 00:29:03,339
Whatever you want. Money?
Half my fee, okay?

187
00:29:03,759 --> 00:29:07,220
No. l'll work for nothing if
you yourself...

188
00:29:08,769 --> 00:29:13,109
Come to Andronnikov Monastery
to fetch me.

189
00:29:13,769 --> 00:29:19,859
Before the community, the
metropolitan, ask me to help you...

190
00:29:20,779 --> 00:29:26,869
Before the brotherhood
before Andrei Rublev.

191
00:29:28,789 --> 00:29:32,250
Then l shall serve you
like a slave...

192
00:29:32,789 --> 00:29:35,369
Like a dog, until the day l die.

193
00:29:35,799 --> 00:29:37,500
What is your name?

194
00:29:38,799 --> 00:29:40,500
Kirill.

195
00:29:48,809 --> 00:29:53,150
Orthodox Christians
Iovers of truth.

196
00:29:53,809 --> 00:29:55,509
How long will this torture go on,
when will...

197
00:29:55,819 --> 00:29:56,640
you end this?

198
00:29:56,819 --> 00:29:59,400
You are thoughtless sinners,
yet you judge.

199
00:30:03,819 --> 00:30:06,400
You faithless heathens!

200
00:30:06,829 --> 00:30:09,410
He has already seven times
atoned for his sins...

201
00:30:10,829 --> 00:30:13,410
for both his sins and yours.

202
00:30:13,829 --> 00:30:16,410
You are incredible
sinners yourselves.

203
00:30:16,839 --> 00:30:19,420
And you judge... but you don't
have God with you.

204
00:30:56,809 --> 00:30:59,390
Rejoice, o young man,
in thy youth...

205
00:30:59,809 --> 00:31:04,150
and let thy heart cheer thee
in the days of thy youth.

206
00:31:04,819 --> 00:31:08,279
Walk in the ways of the thine heart,
an in the sight of thine eyes...

207
00:31:10,819 --> 00:31:16,039
but know that for all these...
God will bring thee into judgment.

208
00:31:26,839 --> 00:31:29,420
Remember now thy Creator in
the days of thy youth...

209
00:31:29,839 --> 00:31:32,420
before the difficult days come...

210
00:31:32,849 --> 00:31:35,430
and the years draw nigh, when
thou shalt say...

211
00:31:35,849 --> 00:31:37,549
''l have no pleasure in them.''

212
00:31:39,849 --> 00:31:43,309
Remember thy Creator...

213
00:31:43,859 --> 00:31:46,440
before the silver cord be loosed. Or
the golden bowl be broken...

214
00:31:46,859 --> 00:31:48,559
or the pitcher shattered
at the fountain...

215
00:31:48,859 --> 00:31:50,559
or the wheel broken at the well.

216
00:31:50,859 --> 00:31:53,440
Then shall the dust return to the
earth as it was...

217
00:31:54,799 --> 00:31:58,259
and the spirit shall return unto
God who gave it.

218
00:31:58,809 --> 00:32:03,150
''Vanity of vanities,'' saith the
preacher; ''All is vanity.''

219
00:32:06,809 --> 00:32:10,269
Kirill, have you seen
Father Nikodim?

220
00:32:12,819 --> 00:32:15,400
Where has he got to since
this morning?

221
00:32:15,819 --> 00:32:21,039
He took my gloves, then disappeared
as though the earth swallowed

222
00:32:21,829 --> 00:32:26,170
l have to chop wood and
the logs are icy.

223
00:32:30,839 --> 00:32:34,299
Why is your candle burning?
It's daylight.

224
00:32:36,839 --> 00:32:38,539
Did you feed my dog?

225
00:32:39,849 --> 00:32:41,549
Did you ask me to?

226
00:32:46,849 --> 00:32:49,430
What's the matter with you?

227
00:32:57,799 --> 00:32:59,500
Go away.

228
00:32:59,799 --> 00:33:04,140
The words of the wise are like
goads, and the words of...

229
00:33:04,799 --> 00:33:08,259
scholars are like well-driven nails
given by one Shepherd.

230
00:33:08,809 --> 00:33:12,269
And further, my son, you should
stay away from these.

231
00:33:13,809 --> 00:33:16,390
N making many books
there is no end...

232
00:33:16,819 --> 00:33:18,519
and much study is wearisome
to the flesh.

233
00:33:18,819 --> 00:33:21,400
Let us hear the conclusion of
the whole matter...

234
00:33:21,819 --> 00:33:24,400
Fear God and keep His
commandments...

235
00:33:24,819 --> 00:33:27,400
for this is man's all.

236
00:33:27,829 --> 00:33:29,529
A messenger has come!

237
00:33:29,829 --> 00:33:33,289
Who has come? A messenger from
Moscow has come.

238
00:33:34,829 --> 00:33:37,410
A messenger has come from
the Grand Prince.

239
00:33:37,839 --> 00:33:39,539
So?

240
00:33:39,839 --> 00:33:41,539
So so.

241
00:33:41,839 --> 00:33:44,420
A messenger from Theophanes
the Greek.

242
00:33:46,849 --> 00:33:50,309
The Grand Prince orders
you to Moscow...

243
00:33:50,849 --> 00:33:54,250
To paint the cathedral of the
Annunciation, with Theophanes.

244
00:34:01,789 --> 00:34:04,369
ls he really Andrei Rublev,
this fellow?

245
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:12,260
Yes, he's Rublev... and l'm Kirill.

246
00:34:13,809 --> 00:34:17,269
Theophanes the Greek says he
wants you in Moscow...

247
00:34:17,809 --> 00:34:19,510
and he wishes to see you.

248
00:34:20,809 --> 00:34:22,510
l thank Theophanes.

249
00:34:23,820 --> 00:34:25,519
Tell him...

250
00:34:27,820 --> 00:34:29,519
that l'll come.

251
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:32,519
l'll come.

252
00:34:34,829 --> 00:34:37,409
My head is splitting!

253
00:34:41,829 --> 00:34:43,530
Bring my horse here.

254
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,539
What is wrong?

255
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:56,119
Choose whichever helpers you like
and be ready tomorrow.

256
00:34:56,780 --> 00:35:01,119
,
Is there a blacksmith here? If not
l'll fall off again.

257
00:35:01,789 --> 00:35:04,369
There is a smithy outside,
beyond the chapel.

258
00:35:05,789 --> 00:35:07,489
Farewell, God-fearing people!

259
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,500
Semyon! Come here!

260
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,500
Come here and help us!

261
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:18,380
Why are you standing?
Come here!

262
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:37,400
Let's go today, shall we,
Danil?

263
00:35:39,829 --> 00:35:44,170
Go quickly, before Theophanes
changes his mind.

264
00:35:44,829 --> 00:35:46,530
l'm not going.

265
00:35:46,829 --> 00:35:48,530
Why aren't you going?

266
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:48,530
How can l manage without you?

267
00:35:53,809 --> 00:35:56,360
As best you can.

268
00:35:58,780 --> 00:36:01,360
l thought we'd go together.

269
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:07,239
Why did you think for me?
l was not invited.

270
00:36:12,789 --> 00:36:14,489
l can't do it without you.

271
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:21,139
You can; you agreed to go
without asking me.

272
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,380
Theophanes simply beckoned.

273
00:36:26,809 --> 00:36:30,269
Don't grieve; you're not
the first, or the last.

274
00:36:31,809 --> 00:36:34,389
Even without you there's plenty
of work for me here.

275
00:36:41,820 --> 00:36:43,519
Thank God for it.

276
00:36:45,829 --> 00:36:48,409
Foma, Aleksei. Let's get ready.

277
00:36:49,829 --> 00:36:51,530
Piotr, you're coming with me.

278
00:37:15,789 --> 00:37:18,369
Did you forget something, Andrei?

279
00:37:21,789 --> 00:37:23,489
l came to say farewell.

280
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:27,500
We've said farewell.

281
00:37:39,809 --> 00:37:42,389
l came to say farewell, but...

282
00:37:47,820 --> 00:37:50,400
it was hard for me before.

283
00:37:53,789 --> 00:37:56,340
Then the devil created enmity
bettween us.

284
00:37:57,760 --> 00:38:00,340
l can't go away like this.

285
00:38:01,769 --> 00:38:03,469
l must make confession.

286
00:38:06,769 --> 00:38:08,469
Will you hear it?

287
00:38:16,780 --> 00:38:19,360
l cannot do anything, Danil...

288
00:38:22,789 --> 00:38:26,250
After living so many years together
in the same cell.

289
00:38:28,789 --> 00:38:33,130
Apart from you, l have on one.

290
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:39,380
l see the world with your eyes.

291
00:38:41,809 --> 00:38:43,510
l hear it with your ears...

292
00:38:45,809 --> 00:38:47,510
With your heart.

293
00:38:56,760 --> 00:39:00,219
l am happy for you, you old fool.

294
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:03,340
lf only knew how happy.

295
00:39:05,769 --> 00:39:09,230
Go to Moscow. Paint; l shall
be proud of you.

296
00:39:09,769 --> 00:39:14,110
The devil tempted me the other
day too. Forgive me.

297
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:44,380
l'll come back, Danil.

298
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:01,400
Where are you going? What
about Vespers?

299
00:40:01,820 --> 00:40:04,400
l'll manage without you.

300
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:07,400
What's wrong with you today,
Kirill?

301
00:40:07,829 --> 00:40:11,289
l'm tired of lying. l'm going back
into the secular world.

302
00:40:13,829 --> 00:40:16,409
Why did we leave the
Trinity Monastery?

303
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:21,420
Andrei, Danil, you are not
saying anything.

304
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:24,420
Because the brothers valued profit
higher than faith.

305
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:27,420
They forgot why they had entered
a monastery.

306
00:40:27,849 --> 00:40:29,550
And now?

307
00:40:29,849 --> 00:40:33,309
We sought to praise God with faith
and work, but what's happened?

308
00:40:33,849 --> 00:40:36,429
The monastery's become a bazaar.

309
00:40:36,860 --> 00:40:39,440
Servant of god, how many souls did
you trade in for monasticism?

310
00:40:39,860 --> 00:40:41,559
Twenty or thirty?

311
00:40:41,860 --> 00:40:45,320
And you ran after the Father
Superior, bargaining.

312
00:40:45,869 --> 00:40:50,210
For ttwo meadows, or even one, you
bought eternal salvation.

313
00:40:50,869 --> 00:40:56,030
You don't need me to tell you, but
you prefer to keep quiet.

314
00:40:56,809 --> 00:41:02,030
Perhaps l would also tolerate all
this loathsomeness if l had talent.

315
00:41:02,820 --> 00:41:06,280
But what talent? Just a slight
ability to paint icons.

316
00:41:06,820 --> 00:41:11,159
God be praised that He
gave me no talent.

317
00:41:11,820 --> 00:41:15,280
l'm happy l'm untalented; l can be
honest and pure before god.

318
00:41:15,829 --> 00:41:17,530
You are taking sin upon
your soul!

319
00:41:17,829 --> 00:41:20,409
l'll tell you something else,
brothers.

320
00:41:20,829 --> 00:41:25,170
What to you want to tell us that
we don't l know already?

321
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,420
Do you know what happens to
your sort? Speak!

322
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:30,539
l won't get offended!

323
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:31,659
Well, l...

324
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:34,420
Get out, you dog!

325
00:41:34,849 --> 00:41:39,190
Out of my sight, you serpent! Rejoin
the secular world, slanderer!

326
00:41:39,849 --> 00:41:41,550
Now do you see?

327
00:41:41,849 --> 00:41:42,670
Kirill!

328
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:45,559
Kirill!

329
00:42:02,809 --> 00:42:07,150
lt is written: ''And Jesus went into
the temple of God...

330
00:42:07,809 --> 00:42:11,269
and cast out all them that sold
and bought in the temple...

331
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:14,400
and overthrew the tables of
the money changers...

332
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:16,519
and the seats of them that
sold doves.''

333
00:42:16,820 --> 00:42:22,039
,
''And said unto them,'' it is written
''My house shall be called...

334
00:42:22,829 --> 00:42:27,170
the house of prayer; but ye have
made it a den of thieves.''

335
00:43:25,820 --> 00:43:29,280
For three years l was cleaning
brushes for Danil...

336
00:43:29,829 --> 00:43:31,530
Before he let me touch an icon.

337
00:43:31,829 --> 00:43:33,530
And then only to clean it.

338
00:43:33,829 --> 00:43:35,530
Don't you trust me?

339
00:43:35,829 --> 00:43:38,409
You're always lying, Foma.

340
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:43,300
Yesterday your robe was sticky;
where were you?

341
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:44,659
At the beehive.

342
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:46,539
But you said you were at
the monastery.

343
00:43:47,849 --> 00:43:49,550
Just look at yourself.

344
00:43:53,820 --> 00:43:56,369
Put mud or something
on your cheek....

345
00:43:56,789 --> 00:43:58,489
Or you will swell, like a hog.

346
00:43:58,789 --> 00:44:01,369
lt's too late now, it's useless.

347
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:07,380
You're constantly making
up stories.

348
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:14,260
l even think you have a disease.

349
00:44:15,809 --> 00:44:17,510
Me? What disease?

350
00:44:21,809 --> 00:44:26,150
There is a disease where a man
lies without stopping.

351
00:44:34,829 --> 00:44:36,530
Look, Foma.

352
00:44:38,829 --> 00:44:40,530
Look, l say.

353
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:46,539
What?

354
00:44:47,840 --> 00:44:50,420
You think know everything so l'm not
going to teach you any more.

355
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:54,360
Why should l learn?

356
00:44:54,780 --> 00:44:57,360
Anyway, l will have to spend three
years cleaning the brushes.

357
00:44:57,780 --> 00:44:59,480
l'm sick and tired of you,
Foma.

358
00:44:59,789 --> 00:45:03,250
Go back to the monastery, go
wherever you want.

359
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:21,260
l can't understand why l took
you as a pupil.

360
00:45:21,809 --> 00:45:24,389
You are always like that. First you
say one thing then another.

361
00:45:24,809 --> 00:45:28,269
You yourself told Theophanes
l was perceptive.

362
00:45:28,809 --> 00:45:32,269
You were different then; you
worked, you didn't lie.

363
00:45:35,820 --> 00:45:39,280
And do you know what
Theophanes said?

364
00:45:39,829 --> 00:45:41,530
''What does it matter it
he's perceptive?''

365
00:45:41,829 --> 00:45:43,530
Whatever Theophanes has said...

366
00:45:43,829 --> 00:45:45,530
l can see blue colors better
than anyone else.

367
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:45,530
You eat too much; how can you paint
with a bloated stomach?

368
00:45:53,809 --> 00:45:57,239
When your stomach's rumbling, how
can your mind work?

369
00:45:58,780 --> 00:46:01,360
The rumbling is the only
sound you hear.

370
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:05,239
You're lucky, Foma. For you,
everything is simple.

371
00:46:05,780 --> 00:46:09,239
lf you are not painting, you are
sleeping or fooling around.

372
00:46:10,789 --> 00:46:15,130
But only by prayer can the soul
transcend the flesh.

373
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:20,380
Would you go to learn from another
teacher instead of me?

374
00:46:20,800 --> 00:46:23,380
Why not, it you tell me to go?

375
00:46:23,800 --> 00:46:26,380
Come on, come on.
Don't be angry.

376
00:46:29,809 --> 00:46:31,510
What's that?

377
00:46:57,769 --> 00:47:02,110
So you've decided to put the
apostle on the left, Andrei.

378
00:47:06,780 --> 00:47:08,480
Did you take glue off the fire?

379
00:47:08,780 --> 00:47:10,480
Did you take glue off the fire?

380
00:47:17,789 --> 00:47:19,489
Perceptive is he?

381
00:47:20,789 --> 00:47:24,250
He should be beaten every
Saturday, like a dog.

382
00:48:45,809 --> 00:48:47,510
You're obstinate, Andrei.

383
00:48:47,809 --> 00:48:52,150
How did you so much? Everyone else
is thinking only of himself.

384
00:48:52,820 --> 00:48:54,460
l say it, Theophanes.

385
00:48:54,750 --> 00:48:57,329
The women of Moscow gave their
hair to the Tatars.

386
00:48:57,760 --> 00:49:00,340
What else could the poor
creatures do?

387
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:04,219
Better to lose their hair than be
tortured. Is that heroic?

388
00:49:04,760 --> 00:49:05,579
lt is.

389
00:49:07,769 --> 00:49:12,989
lt is true that Russian women are
humiliated and unhappy.

390
00:49:13,769 --> 00:49:16,349
lt's not what l mean.

391
00:49:16,780 --> 00:49:20,239
Tell me honestly, are the people
ignorant or not?

392
00:49:21,780 --> 00:49:23,480
Well, are they?

393
00:49:23,780 --> 00:49:26,360
They're ignorant, but whose
fault is that?

394
00:49:26,789 --> 00:49:31,130
lt's their own stupidity. Have you
never sinned through ignorance?

395
00:49:31,789 --> 00:49:33,489
Everyone has.

396
00:49:33,789 --> 00:49:37,250
And l have too. God forgive us
and make us better.

397
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:39,500
Well, never mind.

398
00:49:39,800 --> 00:49:44,139
The Last Judgment is coming;
we'll burn like candles.

399
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:47,380
Mark my words.

400
00:49:48,809 --> 00:49:53,150
Each will accuse the other of his
own sins, to defend himself.

401
00:49:53,809 --> 00:49:59,030
Theophanes, how can you paint with
such ideas, even accept praise?

402
00:50:00,820 --> 00:50:05,159
l have become a hermit and
lived in a cave.

403
00:50:05,820 --> 00:50:07,519
l serve God, not man.

404
00:50:08,829 --> 00:50:14,050
As regards praise, what is praised
today is abused tomorrow.

405
00:50:16,840 --> 00:50:21,179
They will forget you, me,
everything.

406
00:50:22,840 --> 00:50:25,420
All is vanity and ashes. Worse
things have been forgotten.

407
00:50:25,840 --> 00:50:28,420
Humanity has already committed
every stupidity and baseness....

408
00:50:28,849 --> 00:50:30,550
and now it only repeats them.

409
00:50:31,849 --> 00:50:35,309
Everything is an eternal circle and
it repeats and repeats itself.

410
00:50:35,849 --> 00:50:40,190
lf Jesus returned to earth, they
would crucify him again.

411
00:50:40,860 --> 00:50:43,440
N course, if only evil
is remembered....

412
00:50:43,860 --> 00:50:46,440
then you will never be happy in
the sight of God.

413
00:50:46,869 --> 00:50:51,210
Perhaps we must forget some
things; but not all.

414
00:50:52,869 --> 00:50:55,389
l don't know how to say it.

415
00:50:55,809 --> 00:50:57,510
Then be quiet and listen to me.

416
00:50:58,809 --> 00:50:59,630
So.

417
00:51:01,809 --> 00:51:05,269
You think that one can only
do good alone?

418
00:51:06,820 --> 00:51:10,280
Good. Remember the
New Testament.

419
00:51:10,820 --> 00:51:13,400
Jesus taught people
in the temples...

420
00:51:13,829 --> 00:51:19,050
so why did they gather later?
To kill him!

421
00:51:19,829 --> 00:51:22,409
''Crucify him'' they shouted.

422
00:51:23,840 --> 00:51:28,179
And the disciples? Judas sold Him.
Peter denied Him.

423
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:32,300
They all ran away, yet they
were the best.

424
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,539
But they repented.

425
00:51:34,849 --> 00:51:38,309
That was afterwards, when
it was too late.

426
00:51:41,849 --> 00:51:45,309
lt's never too late to repent.

427
00:51:57,800 --> 00:52:00,380
N course, people do evil.

428
00:52:01,809 --> 00:52:04,389
But you can not blame
them altogether.

429
00:52:05,809 --> 00:52:07,510
lt's difficult...

430
00:52:07,809 --> 00:52:09,510
and sinful, l think.

431
00:52:10,820 --> 00:52:14,280
Judas sold the Christ, and remember
who bought him.

432
00:52:14,820 --> 00:52:16,519
People.

433
00:52:16,820 --> 00:52:18,519
And who accused Jesus?

434
00:52:19,820 --> 00:52:21,519
The scribes and Pharisees...

435
00:52:22,829 --> 00:52:26,289
they could not find witnesses,
however hard they tried.

436
00:52:26,829 --> 00:52:29,409
''Who will testify against
this innocent?''

437
00:52:29,829 --> 00:52:32,409
Only later on they found
the traitors.

438
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:34,539
Two were found immediately.

439
00:52:35,840 --> 00:52:37,539
Two, and not one.

440
00:52:38,840 --> 00:52:40,539
There were only ttwo.

441
00:52:40,849 --> 00:52:44,309
The Pharisees were masters
of deceit, educated.

442
00:52:44,849 --> 00:52:47,429
They had studied to gain power...

443
00:52:47,849 --> 00:52:49,550
to take advantage of the
people's ignorance.

444
00:52:50,860 --> 00:52:54,260
We must remind people more often
that they are people.

445
00:52:55,789 --> 00:52:58,369
,
Russians, of the same blood
of the same land.

446
00:52:59,800 --> 00:53:01,500
Evil is everywhere.

447
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:06,260
Someone will always sell you for
thirty pieces of silver.

448
00:53:07,809 --> 00:53:11,269
New misfortunes constantly
befall the peasant...

449
00:53:13,809 --> 00:53:18,150
either Tatars three times an
autumn, or famine, or plague...

450
00:53:18,820 --> 00:53:20,519
and he still keeps on working,
working, working...

451
00:53:20,820 --> 00:53:22,519
meekly bearing his cross.

452
00:53:22,820 --> 00:53:24,519
He does not despair, he is
silent and patient.

453
00:53:24,820 --> 00:53:28,280
He only prays to God for
enough strength.

454
00:53:29,829 --> 00:53:34,170
How could god not forgive
him his ignorance?

455
00:53:36,840 --> 00:53:40,300
You know yourself. You're
tired and discouraged...

456
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:42,539
and suddenly...

457
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:48,300
in the crowd you meet a
human glance...

458
00:53:49,849 --> 00:53:54,130
and everything's lighter, as it
is after Communion.

459
00:53:54,789 --> 00:53:55,610
lsn't it so?

460
00:53:58,789 --> 00:54:01,369
You just spoke of Jesus.

461
00:54:01,789 --> 00:54:04,369
Perhaps He was born and
crucified to reconcile...

462
00:54:04,800 --> 00:54:07,380
God and man.

463
00:54:07,800 --> 00:54:10,380
Jesus came from God, so
He is all-powerful.

464
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:15,139
,
And if He died on the cross
it was predetermined...

465
00:54:15,809 --> 00:54:20,150
and His crucifiKion and death
were God's will.

466
00:54:20,809 --> 00:54:24,269
That would have aroused hatred
not in those who crucified Him...

467
00:54:24,820 --> 00:54:26,519
but in those who loved Him...

468
00:54:26,820 --> 00:54:29,400
if they had been near Him
at that moment...

469
00:54:29,820 --> 00:54:33,280
because they loved Him
as a man only.

470
00:54:33,829 --> 00:54:38,170
,
but if He, of His own will
Ieft them...

471
00:54:38,829 --> 00:54:43,170
He displayed injustice,
or even cruelty.

472
00:54:43,840 --> 00:54:46,420
Maybe those who crucified
Him loved Him...

473
00:54:46,840 --> 00:54:50,300
because they helped in
this divine plan.

474
00:56:11,789 --> 00:56:14,369
Do you understand what you
are saying?

475
00:56:15,789 --> 00:56:20,130
They'll exile you to the
north, man, to renovate the icons.

476
00:56:21,800 --> 00:56:26,139
Am l not right? You too always
say what you think.

477
00:56:27,809 --> 00:56:31,269
But l'm not a monk; l'm free.

478
00:56:47,829 --> 00:56:52,170
THE HOLIDAY
spring 1408

479
00:57:08,780 --> 00:57:10,480
Sergei, over here!

480
00:57:13,789 --> 00:57:16,369
Foma, let's get some logs.

481
00:57:22,789 --> 00:57:26,250
Piotr as probably never seen either
Assumption Cathedral so...

482
00:57:26,800 --> 00:57:28,500
Saint Dimitry Cathedral.

483
00:57:28,800 --> 00:57:32,260
Never mind, he will begin working,
and understand things.

484
00:57:33,809 --> 00:57:35,510
Foma Where are you?

485
00:57:36,809 --> 00:57:38,510
We don't be on time.

486
00:57:38,809 --> 00:57:40,510
lt's okay, we'll be there tomorrow.

487
00:57:40,809 --> 00:57:43,389
No. We'll never finish the Cathedral
of the Assumption by winter.

488
00:57:43,820 --> 00:57:46,400
lt's almost June, Andrei.

489
00:57:54,760 --> 00:57:56,460
What is it?

490
00:57:58,760 --> 00:58:01,340
Quiet! Do you hear it?

491
00:58:02,769 --> 00:58:04,469
Nightingales?

492
00:58:04,769 --> 00:58:06,469
Nothing else?

493
00:58:12,780 --> 00:58:13,599
Come on.

494
00:58:13,780 --> 00:58:15,480
-What is it?
-Come on.

495
00:58:15,780 --> 00:58:17,480
They're practicing witchcraft.

496
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:36,380
Where are you going?

497
00:58:43,809 --> 00:58:45,510
Come to me.

498
00:59:43,800 --> 00:59:45,500
Hold on.

499
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:47,619
Come to me.

500
00:59:47,809 --> 00:59:49,510
Darling.

501
00:59:51,809 --> 00:59:53,510
Take your hand away.

502
00:59:54,809 --> 00:59:56,510
There is an anthill.

503
01:00:06,820 --> 01:00:08,519
Anthill?

504
01:00:09,829 --> 01:00:11,530
Anthill.

505
01:00:11,829 --> 01:00:13,530
Who is this?

506
01:00:13,829 --> 01:00:14,650
l don't know.

507
01:00:14,829 --> 01:00:16,530
Let's go.

508
01:01:55,800 --> 01:02:00,139
lt seemed to me as if a black
snake was hiding himself.

509
01:02:00,809 --> 01:02:02,510
What are you doing?

510
01:02:05,809 --> 01:02:07,510
Let me go!

511
01:02:07,809 --> 01:02:09,510
We'll let you go.

512
01:02:09,809 --> 01:02:14,150
At dawn, we'll hang a stone around
your neck, to help you swim.

513
01:02:17,820 --> 01:02:22,159
Heaven's fire will consume you!
The Last Judgment awaits!

514
01:02:23,829 --> 01:02:29,050
Now we'll tie you to this cross
like Jesus Christ.

515
01:02:30,840 --> 01:02:31,659
No!

516
01:02:31,840 --> 01:02:35,300
What are you doing, men?
You can't to this to me.

517
01:02:36,840 --> 01:02:40,300
This is a sin. At least hang
me upside-down.

518
01:02:41,849 --> 01:02:43,550
Men, brothers!

519
01:02:46,849 --> 01:02:52,070
Leave him here for the night,
unless he ascends again.

520
01:02:53,829 --> 01:02:56,380
He's not going anywhere.

521
01:03:11,809 --> 01:03:13,510
And who is this?

522
01:03:13,809 --> 01:03:14,630
Marfa.

523
01:03:18,820 --> 01:03:23,159
Why did you want to be head down?
It would have been worse.

524
01:03:24,820 --> 01:03:28,280
Why did you threaten us with
fire from heaven?

525
01:03:29,829 --> 01:03:33,289
lt is a sin to go naked and
do what you do.

526
01:03:35,829 --> 01:03:41,920
What sin? Tonight is for
Iovemaking; is love a sin?

527
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:45,420
ls it to tie a man up like this?

528
01:03:45,840 --> 01:03:48,420
You might call the monks...

529
01:03:48,849 --> 01:03:51,429
who would force us to
accept your faith.

530
01:03:52,849 --> 01:03:55,369
Do you think it's easy
to live in fear?

531
01:03:55,789 --> 01:03:58,369
You live in fear because
you know no...

532
01:03:58,789 --> 01:04:00,489
love but bestial love.

533
01:04:00,789 --> 01:04:04,250
Carnality without soul; but love
should be brotherly.

534
01:04:05,800 --> 01:04:09,260
lsn't all love the same?
It's just love.

535
01:04:12,800 --> 01:04:15,380
What are you doing?

536
01:04:26,820 --> 01:04:28,519
Untie me.

537
01:07:40,809 --> 01:07:42,510
Why are you looking at me?

538
01:07:42,809 --> 01:07:44,510
Where were you?

539
01:07:49,820 --> 01:07:51,519
Thank God.

540
01:07:57,760 --> 01:07:59,460
Are these the people?

541
01:08:00,760 --> 01:08:03,340
No, these are strangers.
Don't you see it?

542
01:08:10,769 --> 01:08:13,349
,
There is some onion
if you want it.

543
01:08:21,789 --> 01:08:23,489
Where were you?

544
01:08:27,789 --> 01:08:32,130
These forests are impenetrable;
l'm all scratched.

545
01:08:33,800 --> 01:08:36,380
The local people like it. They are
accustomed to it.

546
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:39,380
For people, everything is a
matter of custom.

547
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:43,380
Old people don't need to think...

548
01:08:43,810 --> 01:08:47,270
for their days pass according
to custom.

549
01:08:48,810 --> 01:08:52,270
But perhaps they consciously
enjoy...

550
01:08:52,819 --> 01:08:55,340
the way the days drag on.

551
01:09:14,770 --> 01:09:17,350
Couldn't you get here before?

552
01:09:17,779 --> 01:09:19,479
No. l couldn't.

553
01:09:19,779 --> 01:09:23,239
That is your sin, your conscience,
your prayers.

554
01:09:29,789 --> 01:09:31,489
Get him, and her!

555
01:09:48,810 --> 01:09:51,390
Why are they doing that?

556
01:09:52,810 --> 01:09:57,149
Because the accursed pagans don't
believe in one God.

557
01:09:59,819 --> 01:10:03,279
Don't look, Sergei. There is
nothing to look at.

558
01:10:03,819 --> 01:10:05,520
Let me go!

559
01:10:06,819 --> 01:10:08,520
Let me go!

560
01:10:08,829 --> 01:10:10,529
You can't see that!

561
01:10:20,840 --> 01:10:23,420
Kich so he shuts up!

562
01:10:27,850 --> 01:10:29,550
Go, go! Don't dawdle!

563
01:10:30,850 --> 01:10:33,430
Help, Fyodor! Help!

564
01:10:40,859 --> 01:10:42,560
Fyodor!

565
01:10:45,859 --> 01:10:47,560
Can't you deal with a woman?

566
01:10:47,869 --> 01:10:50,449
Stop!

567
01:10:52,869 --> 01:10:53,689
Hold her!

568
01:10:54,810 --> 01:10:56,510
Marfa, run!

569
01:11:02,810 --> 01:11:04,510
Catch her!

570
01:11:07,819 --> 01:11:11,279
-Where are you going?
-She will drown herself!

571
01:11:11,819 --> 01:11:13,520
Marfa! Run, Marfa!

572
01:11:19,829 --> 01:11:21,529
Swim, Marfa!

573
01:12:14,819 --> 01:12:20,039
THE LAST JUDGMENT
Summer 1408

574
01:12:20,819 --> 01:12:22,520
Come here!

575
01:12:25,829 --> 01:12:28,409
He's just wasting materials.

576
01:12:28,829 --> 01:12:30,529
Who needs it?

577
01:12:33,840 --> 01:12:34,659
Foma!

578
01:12:34,840 --> 01:12:36,539
What do you want?

579
01:12:36,840 --> 01:12:38,539
Can l go for a swim?

580
01:12:38,840 --> 01:12:40,539
No, you can't.

581
01:12:40,840 --> 01:12:42,539
lt's hot!

582
01:12:43,850 --> 01:12:45,550
Don't be lying. It's not.

583
01:12:45,850 --> 01:12:48,430
Maybe he's really hot.
l'm hot too.

584
01:12:48,850 --> 01:12:50,550
N course, you are working
and he is sitting.

585
01:12:50,850 --> 01:12:51,670
Let him go swim.

586
01:12:51,859 --> 01:12:51,670
Don't spoil him.

587
01:12:53,819 --> 01:12:55,489
Let him be sitting with everyone.

588
01:12:55,789 --> 01:12:57,489
You shut up!

589
01:12:57,800 --> 01:13:00,380
You sleep all day long like a log...

590
01:13:00,800 --> 01:13:04,260
and you come down only to eat
and go to the bathroom.

591
01:13:04,800 --> 01:13:06,500
And have you found a job for me?

592
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:08,500
-You have found what you wanted.
-So what?

593
01:13:08,810 --> 01:13:13,149
Since everyone is sitting here, let
Serezhka be sitting with us to.

594
01:13:13,810 --> 01:13:16,390
lf you had let him go, he would
have been back already.

595
01:13:16,810 --> 01:13:18,510
Give him freedom...

596
01:13:18,819 --> 01:13:20,520
and he will in the water until
he turns blue.

597
01:13:20,819 --> 01:13:23,399
He only thinks that it's hot...

598
01:13:23,819 --> 01:13:25,520
-and that's why he is whining.
-He's not whining,...

599
01:13:25,819 --> 01:13:26,640
you are.

600
01:13:26,819 --> 01:13:27,640
lt was me.

601
01:13:27,829 --> 01:13:30,409
l was the first to say it's hot,
and not Sergei.

602
01:13:30,829 --> 01:13:32,529
Why are you picking on Sergei?

603
01:13:33,829 --> 01:13:34,649
That's it!

604
01:13:34,829 --> 01:13:36,529
You want to go swimming, go!

605
01:13:36,829 --> 01:13:38,529
Go! Why are you sitting?

606
01:13:39,840 --> 01:13:41,539
Go, go!

607
01:13:41,840 --> 01:13:43,539
Here! You see?

608
01:13:43,840 --> 01:13:46,420
Wait! Wait!

609
01:13:48,850 --> 01:13:50,550
Where's Andrei?

610
01:13:50,850 --> 01:13:51,670
Not here?

611
01:13:51,850 --> 01:13:55,250
Not here? This is a fine
state of affairs.

612
01:14:00,789 --> 01:14:03,369
l was our bishop's house
just now.

613
01:14:03,789 --> 01:14:06,369
Such a fuss. Yelling!

614
01:14:07,800 --> 01:14:12,140
He was purple with rage. ''l've
Iost patience!'' He cried.

615
01:14:13,800 --> 01:14:16,380
He meant you. All of you.

616
01:14:16,810 --> 01:14:20,270
,
''For two whole months,'' he said
everything has been ready.

617
01:14:20,810 --> 01:14:22,510
But they haven't started yet.

618
01:14:22,810 --> 01:14:26,270
Nothing is ready; they asked for
so much money, but do nothing.

619
01:14:26,819 --> 01:14:29,399
None of them is working and
nothing is ready.''

620
01:14:29,819 --> 01:14:32,399
Did you ask for a lot of money?

621
01:14:32,819 --> 01:14:34,520
How do l know?

622
01:14:34,829 --> 01:14:40,050
He said, ''l don't care. Danil
Chorny or Andrei Rublev...

623
01:14:40,829 --> 01:14:43,409
it's all the same to me.''

624
01:14:43,829 --> 01:14:45,529
''lt's all the same.''

625
01:14:45,840 --> 01:14:49,300
And he pulled a face like this.

626
01:14:49,840 --> 01:14:52,420
''What do l care about
Andrei Rublev?

627
01:14:55,779 --> 01:14:57,479
By autumn,'' he says...

628
01:14:57,779 --> 01:15:01,239
''l want the cathedral painted,
and that's that!''

629
01:15:01,789 --> 01:15:05,250
He's sent a courier with a complaint
to the Grand Prince.

630
01:15:05,789 --> 01:15:08,369
He's sent a courier to the
Grand Prince.

631
01:15:09,789 --> 01:15:12,369
lt's a complaint about you,
you know.

632
01:15:14,800 --> 01:15:16,500
You haven't started yet.

633
01:15:19,800 --> 01:15:24,140
You'd better hurry up.
Where's Andrei?

634
01:15:24,810 --> 01:15:26,510
He's gone somewhere again.

635
01:15:26,810 --> 01:15:29,390
Can't you start without him?

636
01:15:29,810 --> 01:15:31,510
Go on, start without him.

637
01:15:34,819 --> 01:15:37,399
Why are you smirking? There
are so many of you.

638
01:15:37,819 --> 01:15:40,399
lf he can't make his mind up,
can't one of you?

639
01:15:40,819 --> 01:15:42,520
Two heads are better than one.

640
01:15:43,829 --> 01:15:45,529
Where is Andrei?

641
01:15:48,829 --> 01:15:51,409
l can't go on like that.

642
01:15:51,840 --> 01:15:54,359
Answer me: yes or no?

643
01:15:54,770 --> 01:15:57,350
Yes or no? Wasn't everything
decided in Moscow?

644
01:15:57,770 --> 01:16:02,989
To the smallest detail; the Prince
said everything was in order.

645
01:16:05,779 --> 01:16:11,000
What is not clear? What have we
been discussing for two months?

646
01:16:12,789 --> 01:16:16,250
Explain it to me. l may be old,
l may have lost my wits.

647
01:16:16,789 --> 01:16:21,130
The Last Judgment; either you
accept the task and paint it...

648
01:16:21,800 --> 01:16:24,380
or you refuse the commission.

649
01:16:24,800 --> 01:16:28,260
And if we really refused? If we
went back, Danil?

650
01:16:28,810 --> 01:16:32,270
How shall l face people?
l should die of shame.

651
01:16:34,810 --> 01:16:39,149
We're wasting such good time.
This heat, no rain.

652
01:16:39,819 --> 01:16:42,399
We could have finished the cupola
and the columns.

653
01:16:42,819 --> 01:16:45,399
How wonderfully they could
have been done...

654
01:16:45,819 --> 01:16:49,279
how brightly, and beautifully.
On the right sinners...

655
01:16:49,829 --> 01:16:54,989
boiling in pitch, painted to make
your flesh crawl.

656
01:16:57,770 --> 01:17:01,229
l have thought of a great devil, with
smoke from his nose and eyes.

657
01:17:01,770 --> 01:17:05,229
-lt's not the smoke that matters.
-Then what matters?

658
01:17:05,779 --> 01:17:06,600
l don't know.

659
01:17:06,779 --> 01:17:09,359
-Why aren't you looking at me?
-Because l can't.

660
01:17:26,800 --> 01:17:31,140
l can't paint all that;
it disgusts me.

661
01:17:32,800 --> 01:17:34,500
l don't want to terrify people.
Understand me, Danil.

662
01:17:34,810 --> 01:17:36,510
Collect yourself! Listen!

663
01:17:37,810 --> 01:17:40,390
lt's the Last judgment!

664
01:17:40,810 --> 01:17:42,510
l didn't invent it.

665
01:17:42,810 --> 01:17:45,390
l can't do it. Do as you will,
but l can't.

666
01:17:45,819 --> 01:17:47,520
Why didn't you speak earlier,
in Moscow?

667
01:17:47,819 --> 01:17:50,399
You shouldn't have agreed.

668
01:17:51,819 --> 01:17:50,399
This is dishonest.

669
01:17:53,789 --> 01:17:58,100
l am what l am. You couldn't
teach me integrity.

670
01:18:14,779 --> 01:18:16,479
l don't know what to paint.

671
01:18:17,779 --> 01:18:19,479
What do you mean,
you don't know?

672
01:18:19,779 --> 01:18:22,359
We were ordered to paint the
Last Judgment.

673
01:18:26,789 --> 01:18:28,489
You see...

674
01:18:28,789 --> 01:18:30,489
l think it will be better...

675
01:18:30,789 --> 01:18:33,369
if we don't paint the Last
Judgment at all.

676
01:18:34,800 --> 01:18:36,500
What do you mean?

677
01:18:37,800 --> 01:18:39,500
You know.

678
01:18:40,800 --> 01:18:42,500
l want...

679
01:18:51,819 --> 01:18:42,500
l don't want anything.

680
01:18:53,779 --> 01:18:55,449
-Nothing.
-That's it.

681
01:19:02,760 --> 01:19:05,340
Well, l leaving.

682
01:19:06,760 --> 01:19:08,460
This is no work for me.

683
01:19:09,770 --> 01:19:14,989
Thanks for you kindness and your
slaps; l learned something.

684
01:19:15,770 --> 01:19:18,350
But now l'm going to work
for myself.

685
01:19:21,779 --> 01:19:25,239
They've asked me to paint a
church at Pafnutievo.

686
01:19:25,779 --> 01:19:27,479
Not a great honor, but it's
still an honor.

687
01:19:28,789 --> 01:19:31,369
l'm going to paint the
Last Judgment.

688
01:19:33,789 --> 01:19:35,489
Who will come with me?

689
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:41,500
Well, then, stay...

690
01:19:41,800 --> 01:19:44,380
But don't complain later.

691
01:19:59,819 --> 01:20:02,399
When l was a child...

692
01:20:02,819 --> 01:20:06,279
l speak as a child, l understood as
a child, l thought as a child...

693
01:20:06,819 --> 01:20:09,399
but when l became a man,...

694
01:20:09,829 --> 01:20:12,409
l put away childish things.

695
01:20:12,829 --> 01:20:15,409
For now we see through
a glass, darkly...

696
01:20:15,829 --> 01:20:20,170
but then face to face
now l know in part...

697
01:20:20,840 --> 01:20:22,539
but then shall l know...

698
01:20:22,840 --> 01:20:24,539
even as also l am know.

699
01:20:24,840 --> 01:20:26,539
And now abideth...

700
01:20:26,840 --> 01:20:29,420
faith, hope, and charity...

701
01:20:29,850 --> 01:20:33,310
but the greatest of these
is charity.

702
01:20:33,850 --> 01:20:37,310
Though l speak with the tongues
of men and of angels...

703
01:20:38,859 --> 01:20:40,560
and have not charity...

704
01:20:40,859 --> 01:20:43,439
l am become as sounding brass,
or a tinkling cymbal.

705
01:20:43,859 --> 01:20:46,439
And though l have the
gift of prophecy...

706
01:20:46,859 --> 01:20:49,439
and understand all mysteries,
and all knowledge...

707
01:20:49,869 --> 01:20:52,449
and though l have all faith, so that
l could remove mountains...

708
01:20:52,869 --> 01:20:55,390
and have not charity,
l am nothing.

709
01:20:55,810 --> 01:21:00,149
And though l bestow all my
goods to feed the poor...

710
01:21:00,810 --> 01:21:03,390
and thought l give my body to be
burned, and have not charity...

711
01:21:04,810 --> 01:21:07,390
it profiteth me nothing.

712
01:21:07,819 --> 01:21:12,159
Charity suffereth long, and is kind;
charity envieth not...

713
01:21:12,819 --> 01:21:14,520
charity vaunteth not itself, is
not puffed up...

714
01:21:15,829 --> 01:21:17,529
doth not behave itself unseemly...

715
01:21:17,829 --> 01:21:19,529
seeketh not her own, is not
easily provoked,...

716
01:21:19,829 --> 01:21:21,529
thinketh no evil.

717
01:21:21,829 --> 01:21:25,289
rejoiceth not in iniquity, but
rejoiceth in the truth...

718
01:21:25,840 --> 01:21:28,420
beareth all things...

719
01:21:28,840 --> 01:21:31,420
believeth all things, hopeth
all things,...

720
01:21:31,840 --> 01:21:33,539
endureth all things.

721
01:21:35,850 --> 01:21:37,550
Charity never faileth...

722
01:21:40,850 --> 01:21:43,430
but whether there be prophecies,
they shall fail...

723
01:21:43,850 --> 01:21:45,550
whether there be tongues,
they shall cease...

724
01:21:45,859 --> 01:21:48,439
whether there be knowledge,
it shall vanish away.

725
01:21:48,859 --> 01:21:51,439
For we know in part...

726
01:21:53,829 --> 01:21:56,380
Princess, is that nice?

727
01:21:57,800 --> 01:21:59,500
lt's sinful to splash milk.

728
01:22:00,800 --> 01:22:02,500
Such a naughtiness.

729
01:22:05,810 --> 01:22:07,510
Why is it sinful?

730
01:22:07,810 --> 01:22:10,390
Because...wipe it off.

731
01:22:10,810 --> 01:22:13,390
But it will dry by itself
in a minute.

732
01:22:13,819 --> 01:22:16,399
Let's walk by the stream.

733
01:22:20,819 --> 01:22:24,279
Let me go, Stepan, or l'll send
you to the stables.

734
01:22:27,829 --> 01:22:31,289
How do you like it? l couldn't imagine
it better. It's light, beautiful.

735
01:22:31,840 --> 01:22:35,300
lt's light.

736
01:22:46,850 --> 01:22:48,550
lt's light.

737
01:22:50,850 --> 01:22:54,250
Take her out. Her nurses
have spoiled her.

738
01:22:54,789 --> 01:22:56,489
l say!

739
01:22:56,789 --> 01:22:59,369
No one can build a mansion
better than us.

740
01:22:59,800 --> 01:23:02,380
Who could paint like that?

741
01:23:03,800 --> 01:23:07,260
Only Mitiai can do this directly,
without tracing.

742
01:23:07,800 --> 01:23:09,500
lt's like a bird singind.

743
01:23:09,810 --> 01:23:13,270
Look. Maybe it is like a
bird singind.

744
01:23:13,810 --> 01:23:18,149
l don't care. l can sleep on the hay.
You are the Grand Prince.

745
01:23:19,819 --> 01:23:21,520
Don't you like it?

746
01:23:21,819 --> 01:23:23,520
l'll tell you this. It should
be repainted.

747
01:23:23,819 --> 01:23:27,279
Walls, ceiling, everything:
brighter, stronger colors.

748
01:23:28,829 --> 01:23:31,409
l've been in this trade for
forty years.

749
01:23:31,829 --> 01:23:32,649
lt's not the years that matter...

750
01:23:32,829 --> 01:23:34,529
but your ability to glorify the
Grand Prince with your work.

751
01:23:35,829 --> 01:23:37,529
That's enough. Go.

752
01:23:39,840 --> 01:23:41,539
We won't redo anything.

753
01:23:42,840 --> 01:23:45,420
lt's time to go. We
have another job.

754
01:23:45,840 --> 01:23:47,539
They are waiting for us
in Zvenigorod.

755
01:23:48,850 --> 01:23:49,670
Where?

756
01:23:49,850 --> 01:23:52,430
At your brother's. They have
the stone already.

