,
l don't know. Forever
most likely.

1008
02:12:28,590 --> 02:12:31,170
Yet how beautiful all this is.

1009
02:12:40,600 --> 02:12:42,300
lt's snowing.

1010
02:12:47,609 --> 02:12:52,829
Nothing is more terrible than snow
falling in a temple.

1011
02:13:48,600 --> 02:13:53,819
THE CHARITY
Winter 1412

1012
02:16:38,639 --> 02:16:41,219
The apples are all rotten.

1013
02:16:45,649 --> 02:16:49,110
ln all my years, l've never seen
such a famine.

1014
02:16:49,649 --> 02:16:52,229
We are slowly dying out.
Lord have pity on us.

1015
02:16:55,620 --> 02:16:58,170
Mefody is bringing someone again.

1016
02:17:07,600 --> 02:17:10,180
Mefody, you should not be
the gate-keeper...

1017
02:17:10,600 --> 02:17:13,180
because you will let the people the
whole neighborhood in here to eat.

1018
02:17:14,610 --> 02:17:17,190
-Sit down, man of God.
-Thank you.

1019
02:17:18,610 --> 02:17:20,309
To eat!

1020
02:17:20,610 --> 02:17:24,069
You can't feed all the
hungry people.

1021
02:17:26,620 --> 02:17:29,200
There is no one in the
neighborhood.

1022
02:17:29,620 --> 02:17:32,200
The villages are deserted.

1023
02:17:36,629 --> 02:17:39,209
Everyone has left Khotkovo.

1024
02:17:42,639 --> 02:17:44,340
The people of Semyonovka
have fled.

1025
02:17:44,639 --> 02:17:46,340
They've fled, they've fled!

1026
02:17:46,639 --> 02:17:49,219
lt's true. l passed Semyonovka
this morning.

1027
02:17:49,639 --> 02:17:51,340
ln Vladimir it is even worse.

1028
02:17:51,649 --> 02:17:54,229
No harvest for three years;
everyone has fled.

1029
02:17:54,649 --> 02:17:56,290
Those who stayed are eating mice.

1030
02:17:56,579 --> 02:17:58,280
Why are you whispering?

1031
02:17:58,590 --> 02:18:01,170
l'm not whispering. l have a cold.
l spent a night in a lake.

1032
02:18:01,590 --> 02:18:03,290
Why was that?

1033
02:18:03,590 --> 02:18:08,809
,
Wolves chased me; l fled to the lake
praying they wouldn't follow.

1034
02:18:09,600 --> 02:18:11,299
l was starting like that till dawn.

1035
02:18:11,600 --> 02:18:14,180
When l got out, l was
completely numb.

1036
02:18:14,600 --> 02:18:18,940
l've been sick for two weeks and
l'm shivering all over.

1037
02:18:19,610 --> 02:18:22,190
-So you're from Vladimir.
-So used to live there.

1038
02:18:22,610 --> 02:18:25,190
Someone else from
Vladimir is here.

1039
02:18:25,610 --> 02:18:29,069
Andrei Rublev. Here you
heard of him?

1040
02:18:30,620 --> 02:18:34,079
He has sinned, and now
he is atoning.

1041
02:18:34,620 --> 02:18:36,319
He has brought a holy fool with
him from Vladimir.

1042
02:18:36,620 --> 02:18:38,319
A mute girl.

1043
02:18:38,629 --> 02:18:41,209
Now they are silent together.

1044
02:18:50,639 --> 02:18:53,219
Though she is a holy fool, she
knows where to...

1045
02:18:53,639 --> 02:18:53,219
get better food.

1046
02:18:55,610 --> 02:18:57,280
He has brought her...

1047
02:18:57,579 --> 02:19:01,040
so that he may always
remember his sin.

1048
02:19:05,590 --> 02:19:08,170
Can you call it holiness?

1049
02:19:10,590 --> 02:19:12,290
And Rublev's guild?

1050
02:19:12,590 --> 02:19:14,290
lt fell apart.

1051
02:19:15,600 --> 02:19:19,059
Some were killed by Tatars...

1052
02:19:19,600 --> 02:19:22,180
others were driven away.

1053
02:19:22,600 --> 02:19:24,299
ls Danil alive?

1054
02:19:24,600 --> 02:19:28,940
Some say he went north,
others say he died.

1055
02:19:30,610 --> 02:19:33,190
So he's given up his craft?

1056
02:19:33,610 --> 02:19:35,309
Aren't you Kirill?

1057
02:19:40,620 --> 02:19:43,200
Kirill, is it you?

1058
02:20:00,569 --> 02:20:03,149
Father! Master! Kirill has
come back!

1059
02:20:09,579 --> 02:20:13,920
Father! Let your prodigal son
Kirill back in!

1060
02:20:17,590 --> 02:20:20,170
You didn't ask me if you
could leave...

1061
02:20:20,590 --> 02:20:22,290
and now you want to come back?

1062
02:20:22,600 --> 02:20:24,299
You didn't like it in the
secular world?

1063
02:20:24,600 --> 02:20:26,299
No, l won't take you in.

1064
02:20:26,600 --> 02:20:29,180
My God, why hast thou
forsaken me?

1065
02:20:29,600 --> 02:20:32,180
Now you want back into the
den of thieves...

1066
02:20:32,610 --> 02:20:34,309
to the money-changers
and dove-sellers.

1067
02:20:34,610 --> 02:20:38,069
You think because l am old, l have
forgotten about it.

1068
02:20:38,610 --> 02:20:41,190
Begone! Go back to where
you came from!

1069
02:20:41,620 --> 02:20:44,200
There is no truth in the world.
The devil tempted me.

1070
02:20:44,620 --> 02:20:47,200
l can't continue sinning...

1071
02:20:47,620 --> 02:20:50,200
and without sin you cannot live
in the secular world.

1072
02:20:50,620 --> 02:20:54,079
There is sin and dirt all around.

1073
02:20:54,629 --> 02:20:57,149
Accept my penitence and l will
kiss your feet.

1074
02:20:57,559 --> 02:21:01,020
You were always eloquent, but
you won't move me, Kirill.

1075
02:21:02,569 --> 02:21:06,030
lf you knew how l've suffered,
what l've endured...

1076
02:21:06,569 --> 02:21:10,030
if you knew what evil l've seen,
you would forgive me...

1077
02:21:10,579 --> 02:21:12,280
but l will never forgive myself.

1078
02:21:12,579 --> 02:21:16,040
You're not guilty before me,
but before God.

1079
02:21:18,590 --> 02:21:22,049
Remain here; but to
eKpiate your sin...

1080
02:21:22,590 --> 02:21:26,049
you must copy out the Scriptures
fifteen times.

1081
02:21:26,590 --> 02:21:29,170
Take the late Nikodim's cell.

1082
02:21:29,600 --> 02:21:32,180
Thank you! Thank you, God!

1083
02:21:35,600 --> 02:21:39,059
How wonderful! Thank you,
father, thank you!

1084
02:25:08,549 --> 02:25:12,010
Hey, it's bad to eat dirty meat.

1085
02:25:34,569 --> 02:25:37,149
Brothers, what's going on?

1086
02:25:37,579 --> 02:25:40,159
l'll go to tell Father Nikodim.

1087
02:26:41,639 --> 02:26:44,219
A good Russian. She eats
horsemeat.

1088
02:26:45,649 --> 02:26:48,229
Do you want to come with me?
You'll be my wife.

1089
02:26:52,649 --> 02:26:48,229
l have seven wives, but no
Russian wife.

1090
02:26:55,620 --> 02:26:59,049
You will eat horsemeat every
day, drink horse milk,...

1091
02:26:59,590 --> 02:27:01,290
wear coins in hair.

1092
02:28:00,590 --> 02:28:04,049
Russian wife for Tatar
husband is never dirty.

1093
02:29:10,590 --> 02:29:12,290
Girl! Come with us!

1094
02:29:28,610 --> 02:29:31,190
Come! Give me your hand!

1095
02:30:26,600 --> 02:30:28,299
Do you hear me, Andrei?

1096
02:30:42,620 --> 02:30:44,319
Don't you recognize me?

1097
02:31:10,579 --> 02:31:14,040
Don't grieve, they'll her go.

1098
02:31:16,579 --> 02:31:20,040
They won't dare harm a holy
fool. It's a sin.

1099
02:31:55,590 --> 02:32:01,659
THE BELL Spring-Summer-Autumn
Winter-Spring 1423-1424

1100
02:32:27,590 --> 02:32:29,290
,
Is this the home of Nikolka
the bell-maker?

1101
02:32:31,590 --> 02:32:32,409
lt is.

1102
02:32:32,590 --> 02:32:34,290
ls he your father?

1103
02:32:35,600 --> 02:32:36,420
Yes.

1104
02:32:36,600 --> 02:32:38,299
Then call him.

1105
02:32:39,600 --> 02:32:41,299
-He's not here.
-Where is he?

1106
02:32:42,600 --> 02:32:44,299
He's dead.

1107
02:32:47,610 --> 02:32:51,950
The plague took them all:
mother, sister, father.

1108
02:32:52,610 --> 02:32:51,950
And where does Gravrila the
bell-maker live?

1109
02:32:55,579 --> 02:32:59,010
Gravrila? He's dead, too.

1110
02:32:59,549 --> 02:33:04,770
So is Kasian, and the Tatars led
Ivashka away last year.

1111
02:33:05,559 --> 02:33:09,020
Only Fyodor is left. Go to
him; the fifth hut.

1112
02:33:10,559 --> 02:33:13,139
But you should hurry; Fyodor's
in bed with the plague.

1113
02:33:13,569 --> 02:33:17,909
He can't open his eyes. He will
pass away at any moment.

1114
02:33:29,579 --> 02:33:33,920
l can't stand it any more. Where
else can we look? Let's go home.

1115
02:33:34,590 --> 02:33:37,170
Get up. You aren't going home.

1116
02:33:42,600 --> 02:33:46,059
ls there no one left to
cast the bell?

1117
02:33:47,600 --> 02:33:49,299
Take me with you.

1118
02:33:51,600 --> 02:33:49,299
Let me cast the bell for you.

1119
02:33:55,569 --> 02:33:57,239
Are you mad, boy?

1120
02:33:57,540 --> 02:33:59,239
Take to the Prince.

1121
02:33:59,549 --> 02:34:02,129
Honestly, l can make everything
very well for you.

1122
02:34:02,549 --> 02:34:07,770
You won't find anyone better
than me; they're all dead.

1123
02:34:08,549 --> 02:34:10,250
Go to hell!

1124
02:34:10,559 --> 02:34:14,899
Okay! But l know the secret of
bell-making, and l won't tell.

1125
02:34:15,559 --> 02:34:18,139
What you saying?

1126
02:34:18,559 --> 02:34:22,899
l know the secret. My father knew
the secret of bell making.

1127
02:34:23,569 --> 02:34:27,909
Before he died, he passed it to me.
No one else knows, except me.

1128
02:34:30,579 --> 02:34:34,040
My father died and passed
me the secret.

1129
02:34:35,579 --> 02:34:38,159
Shall we take him?

1130
02:34:38,579 --> 02:34:40,280
What secret?

1131
02:34:40,590 --> 02:34:43,170
Do you want the Prince
to flay us?

1132
02:34:43,590 --> 02:34:45,290
He's lying about the secret.

1133
02:34:45,590 --> 02:34:47,290
The worse for him!

1134
02:34:48,590 --> 02:34:51,170
-What ism your name?
-Boriska.

1135
02:34:51,600 --> 02:34:53,299
Come here!

1136
02:34:59,540 --> 02:35:00,360
Mount!

1137
02:35:07,549 --> 02:35:09,250
What about the hut?

1138
02:35:12,549 --> 02:35:14,250
Did you persuade him?

1139
02:35:58,600 --> 02:36:00,299
Shall we did here?

1140
02:36:00,600 --> 02:36:02,299
We can it here.

1141
02:36:02,600 --> 02:36:05,180
But it would be more convenient to
do it closer to the Bell-tower...

1142
02:36:05,600 --> 02:36:08,180
So that we won't have to drag this
heavy thing far.

1143
02:36:08,610 --> 02:36:11,190
Can't we dig here?
Let's do it here.

1144
02:36:16,620 --> 02:36:17,440
Mark it out.

1145
02:36:20,620 --> 02:36:23,200
Let's dig together, shall we?

1146
02:36:26,629 --> 02:36:29,209
We're bell-casters, not diggers.

1147
02:36:29,629 --> 02:36:31,329
Why should we be digging?

1148
02:36:32,629 --> 02:36:34,329
You know what my father said...

1149
02:36:35,629 --> 02:36:38,209
before he died?

1150
02:36:39,639 --> 02:36:43,100
''Bell-casters must dig the
casting-pit.''

1151
02:36:44,639 --> 02:36:48,979
l only understood that in my old age,''
he said, and died.

1152
02:36:51,649 --> 02:36:55,110
l don't know what Nikolka said, but
l'm not going to dig.

1153
02:36:59,590 --> 02:37:02,170
Call us when you need us.

1154
02:37:03,600 --> 02:37:05,299
Well?

1155
02:38:12,600 --> 02:38:14,299
Did you find it?

1156
02:38:16,600 --> 02:38:19,180
There is no need to look for it.
Here it is.

1157
02:38:39,629 --> 02:38:43,090
No, it's not the right clay.

1158
02:38:43,629 --> 02:38:46,209
-We always took it here.
-Then you are fools.

1159
02:38:46,629 --> 02:38:48,329
The clay is very good.

1160
02:38:48,629 --> 02:38:51,209
-Andreika, isn't the clay bad?
-Yes, it's bad.

1161
02:38:51,639 --> 02:38:53,340
You see? Come on.

1162
02:38:59,579 --> 02:39:02,159
We'll search until we
find good clay.

1163
02:39:09,590 --> 02:39:13,049
Stepan, perhaps we shouldn't
have done this.

1164
02:39:14,590 --> 02:39:17,170
Come on. Look what clay we
have found.

1165
02:39:18,600 --> 02:39:22,940
How hard we've worked, and now
we've found a new spot.

1166
02:39:23,600 --> 02:39:25,299
lt's not the right kind.

1167
02:39:27,610 --> 02:39:31,950
lt's the end of August, and we
have not found the clay yet.

1168
02:39:32,610 --> 02:39:35,190
Think about yourself.
l'm sorry for you.

1169
02:39:35,610 --> 02:39:37,309
l've managed all these years
without your pity.

1170
02:39:39,620 --> 02:39:42,200
Let's go back, Boriska.

1171
02:39:42,620 --> 02:39:44,319
l can't. l know that's not
the right clay.

1172
02:39:44,620 --> 02:39:46,319
Then what is right?

1173
02:39:46,629 --> 02:39:48,329
l know what is.

1174
02:39:53,629 --> 02:39:56,149
l don't need people like you.

1175
02:39:57,569 --> 02:39:59,270
l can manage without you.

1176
02:39:59,569 --> 02:40:01,270
l don't need such people!

1177
02:41:04,569 --> 02:41:06,270
Andreika!

1178
02:41:07,569 --> 02:41:09,270
Semyon!

1179
02:41:11,579 --> 02:41:13,280
l have found it!

1180
02:41:18,579 --> 02:41:21,159
Uncle Fyodor! l've found it!

1181
02:41:27,590 --> 02:41:29,290
The clay! Uncles Seymon!

1182
02:41:29,600 --> 02:41:31,299
Stepan!

1183
02:41:32,600 --> 02:41:35,180
We've found the good clay,
Stepan!

1184
02:41:36,600 --> 02:41:38,299
Here is the clay!

1185
02:41:38,600 --> 02:41:40,299
l have found the clay, Stepan!

1186
02:41:47,610 --> 02:41:49,309
Andreika! Andreika!

1187
02:41:52,620 --> 02:41:55,200
Where are you all?

1188
02:42:06,569 --> 02:42:08,270
Boriska! Boriska!

1189
02:42:09,569 --> 02:42:11,270
-What?
-Shall l dig in?

1190
02:42:11,569 --> 02:42:13,270
l'm coming.

1191
02:42:13,569 --> 02:42:15,270
What are you saying?

1192
02:42:16,579 --> 02:42:18,280
l'm coming!

1193
02:42:18,579 --> 02:42:20,280
Where's Nikolai?

1194
02:42:20,579 --> 02:42:22,280
He left this morning
to fetch wood.

1195
02:42:22,579 --> 02:42:24,280
-lt should be here already.
-He'll be back by evening.

1196
02:42:24,579 --> 02:42:27,159
The evening? l need to
reinforce it now.

1197
02:42:30,590 --> 02:42:33,170
To the devil with your Nikolai,
he's an idiot.

1198
02:42:40,600 --> 02:42:44,059
Why are you standing there?
Work!

1199
02:42:44,600 --> 02:42:46,299
-The merchants don't agree.
-What do you mean?

1200
02:42:46,610 --> 02:42:48,309
They have tripled the price.

1201
02:42:48,610 --> 02:42:49,430
They say it's still cheap.

1202
02:42:49,610 --> 02:42:50,430
But it. What else can we do?

1203
02:42:50,610 --> 02:42:51,430
But it at this price?

1204
02:42:51,610 --> 02:42:51,430
Buy, l say!

1205
02:42:55,579 --> 02:42:57,250
The Prince will flay you.
We'll ruin him.

1206
02:42:59,549 --> 02:43:02,129
l no longer care. Buy it.

1207
02:43:04,559 --> 02:43:06,260
You're in the way, Father.
It's dangerous.

1208
02:43:10,559 --> 02:43:13,139
Don't dig in without me.

1209
02:43:13,569 --> 02:43:17,909
-Boriska!
-Just one moment.

1210
02:43:18,569 --> 02:43:21,149
The cast won't hold; it needs
another layer.

1211
02:43:21,569 --> 02:43:24,149
Another layer? You should have
applied the clay already.

1212
02:43:24,579 --> 02:43:26,280
You haven't put up the frame yet!

1213
02:43:27,579 --> 02:43:31,920
lt needs reinforcing, but there
are no more twigs.

1214
02:43:32,579 --> 02:43:34,280
We're not going to reinforce it.
We start firing tonight.

1215
02:43:34,590 --> 02:43:37,170
ls he kidding?

1216
02:43:37,590 --> 02:43:39,290
,
If we don't reinforce the cast
it won't hold.

1217
02:43:39,590 --> 02:43:41,290
lt will crack and our work
will be wasted.

1218
02:43:41,590 --> 02:43:43,290
,
If it with snows and we can't fire
won't our work be wasted, too?

1219
02:43:43,600 --> 02:43:45,299
They'll flog me, not you.

1220
02:43:45,600 --> 02:43:47,299
The cast won't hold like this.

1221
02:43:47,600 --> 02:43:49,299
Apply the clay.

1222
02:43:51,600 --> 02:43:53,299
Do you hear me?

1223
02:43:54,610 --> 02:43:56,250
l won't do it.

1224
02:43:57,540 --> 02:44:01,879
You won't Then get out!
Andreika, apply the clay.

1225
02:44:02,549 --> 02:44:04,250
He won't do it, either.

1226
02:44:05,549 --> 02:44:07,250
Are you going to apply the clay?

1227
02:44:07,549 --> 02:44:09,250
The metal will burst the mold.

1228
02:44:09,549 --> 02:44:11,250
lt needs reinforcement.

1229
02:44:11,559 --> 02:44:15,020
Will you obey me? Who is in
charge here?

1230
02:44:15,559 --> 02:44:17,260
lt needs reinforcement.

1231
02:44:18,559 --> 02:44:20,260
Fyodor!

1232
02:44:21,569 --> 02:44:23,270
Fyodor!

1233
02:44:24,569 --> 02:44:28,030
Flog him! He refuses to work.

1234
02:44:28,569 --> 02:44:32,030
He won't obey my orders.

1235
02:44:32,579 --> 02:44:36,040
l'll show you who's in charge!

1236
02:44:36,579 --> 02:44:39,159
Your father treated us better.

1237
02:44:39,579 --> 02:44:43,920
You remember him? Then flog him
in my father's name.

1238
02:44:44,590 --> 02:44:47,170
All right, apply the clay.

1239
02:44:53,600 --> 02:44:56,120
Start the work without me.

1240
02:44:56,540 --> 02:44:58,239
But we're waiting for you.

1241
02:44:58,540 --> 02:45:00,239
Start without me.

1242
02:45:03,540 --> 02:45:06,120
Rest, sleep a little.

1243
02:45:13,549 --> 02:45:16,129
Why are you staring at me?

1244
02:45:22,559 --> 02:45:26,020
Lost your tongue? Are you deaf?

1245
02:45:35,569 --> 02:45:37,270
Are you sorry for him?

1246
02:45:42,579 --> 02:45:46,920
Go and console him; that's
what a monk is for.

1247
02:45:52,590 --> 02:45:55,170
O Lord. O Queen of Heaven...

1248
02:46:59,590 --> 02:47:06,559
l can't understand how the Grand
Prince trusted him with all this.

1249
02:47:17,610 --> 02:47:19,309
Boriska! Wake up!

1250
02:47:22,610 --> 02:47:24,309
l've started the firing.

1251
02:47:25,620 --> 02:47:27,319
Why did you start without me?

1252
02:47:27,620 --> 02:47:31,079
l told you to wake me.

1253
02:47:36,629 --> 02:47:39,209
Only know when to start.

1254
02:47:39,629 --> 02:47:43,969
Fyodor, the Prince's men have come,
and they want to see you.

1255
02:47:54,649 --> 02:47:56,290
What heat!

1256
02:48:03,590 --> 02:48:05,290
What heat!

1257
02:48:25,610 --> 02:48:27,309
That's enough.

1258
02:48:35,620 --> 02:48:40,840
Not enough sliver; tell the Prince
not be so miserly.

1259
02:48:41,629 --> 02:48:43,329
Out Grand Prince is
never miserly.

1260
02:48:43,629 --> 02:48:46,209
l don't care. l need another
eighteen pounds of sliver.

1261
02:48:46,629 --> 02:48:49,209
What's eighteen pounds of sliver,
more or less?

1262
02:48:49,629 --> 02:48:52,209
Who knows the secret of
bell-casting, l or you?

1263
02:48:52,639 --> 02:48:52,209
Tell the Prince not to be
miserly. We need...

1264
02:48:55,610 --> 02:48:57,280
another sixteen pounds.

1265
02:48:57,579 --> 02:48:59,280
Are you mad?

1266
02:48:59,579 --> 02:49:02,159
l'll get all the silver l want
from the Prince.

1267
02:49:06,590 --> 02:49:09,170
lmagine, if after this it
doesn't ring!

1268
02:49:14,590 --> 02:49:16,290
Watch out.

1269
02:49:33,610 --> 02:49:35,309
l recognize him!

1270
02:49:35,610 --> 02:49:37,309
Beat him! Beat him!

1271
02:49:42,620 --> 02:49:46,079
Are you mad? To attack
someone like that.

1272
02:49:47,629 --> 02:49:50,209
You've mistaken him for another.

1273
02:49:50,629 --> 02:49:54,090
l'm not mistaken. l recognize
you, Judas.

1274
02:49:54,629 --> 02:49:58,030
How handsome he used to be then.
Now he has lost his looks.

1275
02:49:58,569 --> 02:50:02,909
Thanks to him, l spent ten
years in prison...

1276
02:50:03,579 --> 02:50:06,159
and they cut off half my tongue.

1277
02:50:08,579 --> 02:50:10,280
l'll kill him!

1278
02:50:17,590 --> 02:50:19,290
l'll kill him!

1279
02:50:19,590 --> 02:50:21,290
l'll kill him!

1280
02:50:28,600 --> 02:50:32,059
He's innocent, brother. He's
betrayed no one.

1281
02:50:32,600 --> 02:50:36,059
l swear by the Holy Cross. Lord,
why this punishment?

1282
02:50:41,610 --> 02:50:44,190
Strike me, but don't touch him.

1283
02:50:45,620 --> 02:50:47,319
Get up.

1284
02:50:54,629 --> 02:50:56,270
You're heavy.

1285
02:50:59,559 --> 02:51:02,139
The Prince's jester died.

1286
02:51:02,569 --> 02:51:06,909
They wanted me to go, but l'd
rather be a carpenter.

1287
02:51:09,569 --> 02:51:12,149
l recognize him.

1288
02:51:15,579 --> 02:51:17,280
He denounced me.

1289
02:51:19,579 --> 02:51:21,280
Give me something to drink.

1290
02:51:49,610 --> 02:51:52,190
There are worse things than that.

1291
02:52:07,569 --> 02:52:10,149
Andreika, stand aside.

1292
02:52:21,579 --> 02:52:24,159
Why stand there? Work!

1293
02:52:31,590 --> 02:52:32,409
OO Add some more,...

1294
02:52:32,590 --> 02:52:34,290
add some more!

1295
02:52:34,590 --> 02:52:36,290
Come on!

1296
02:52:36,590 --> 02:52:38,290
Boriska, where is he?

1297
02:53:03,559 --> 02:53:06,139
Boriska, the second
furnace is ready.

1298
02:53:12,559 --> 02:53:15,139
Go, go! We're all ready.

1299
02:53:22,569 --> 02:53:23,389
Open!

1300
02:53:45,600 --> 02:53:48,180
Everything is ready.
Shall we begin?

1301
02:53:49,600 --> 02:53:50,420
Come on!

1302
02:54:01,549 --> 02:54:05,889
lt's coming, Boriska! It's coming!
It's coming.

1303
02:54:12,559 --> 02:54:14,260
God, help me.

1304
02:57:58,579 --> 02:58:01,159
What a day tomorrow will be!

1305
02:58:04,590 --> 02:58:06,290
We should get some sleep.

1306
02:58:16,600 --> 02:58:19,180
Boriska! Let's go, shall we?

1307
02:58:19,600 --> 02:58:21,299
Just a moment.

1308
02:59:11,590 --> 02:59:14,170
This is what happened, Andrei.

1309
02:59:19,600 --> 02:59:22,180
l've thought it over and l've
decided to tell you.

1310
02:59:25,600 --> 02:59:29,059
You know how much l envied.
Envy just gnawed at me.

1311
02:59:30,610 --> 02:59:33,190
lt was inside me like a poison.

1312
02:59:33,610 --> 02:59:37,950
l couldn't stand it any longer,
that's why l left.

1313
02:59:38,620 --> 02:59:42,079
l left because of you.

1314
02:59:42,620 --> 02:59:46,079
When l heard you had given up
painting, the envy went.

1315
02:59:46,620 --> 02:59:49,200
My heart grew lighter.
Then l forgot.

1316
02:59:50,629 --> 02:59:52,329
l only want to copy the
Scriptures before l die.

1317
02:59:52,629 --> 02:59:56,030
The Father Superior is strict...

1318
02:59:56,569 --> 02:59:59,149
and his punishment is not easy
in my old age.

1319
02:59:59,569 --> 03:00:02,149
l'm afraid l won't have enough
time to finish my task.

1320
03:00:02,569 --> 03:00:05,149
Why am l repenting? Why should
l repent to you?

1321
03:00:05,579 --> 03:00:07,280
You yourself are a greater
sinner than l.

1322
03:00:07,579 --> 03:00:11,040
Yes, yes, greater than l.

1323
03:00:11,579 --> 03:00:13,280
What am l? A humble worm;
nothing is demanded of me.

1324
03:00:13,579 --> 03:00:15,280
But you, what are you?

1325
03:00:15,590 --> 03:00:18,170
For what sacred deed did God
give you your talent?

1326
03:00:18,590 --> 03:00:21,170
Lord, l don't want to say this.

1327
03:00:21,590 --> 03:00:24,170
l know Nikon has sent a third
messenger to you...

1328
03:00:24,600 --> 03:00:27,180
to persuade you to come back
to paint the Trinity.

1329
03:00:27,600 --> 03:00:29,299
And you sent them all back. You
wouldn't even talk to them.

1330
03:00:29,600 --> 03:00:32,180
l'll tell you the truth. l won't lie.

1331
03:00:32,600 --> 03:00:36,059
Then, in my dirty soul, there,
in the very depth of it...

1332
03:00:36,610 --> 03:00:39,190
there was a tiny flicker of joy.

1333
03:00:39,610 --> 03:00:41,309
And now...

1334
03:00:43,610 --> 03:00:47,069
my life is ending; my soul
calls out for rest.

1335
03:00:48,620 --> 03:00:51,200
Nikon doesn't care a bit
for you life.

1336
03:00:51,620 --> 03:00:51,200
He wants you here, to glorify and
strengthen his power with your talent.

1337
03:00:55,590 --> 03:00:58,139
Never mind Nikon, but
listen to me.

1338
03:00:59,559 --> 03:01:03,020
Go to the Trinity cathedral and
paint, paint, paint!

1339
03:01:03,569 --> 03:01:07,909
Don't burden your soul, for it is an
awful sin to deny the divine spark.

1340
03:01:09,569 --> 03:01:13,030
lf Theophanes were alive, wouldn't
he say the same thing?

1341
03:01:15,579 --> 03:01:19,040
Look at me, look at the ungifted one.
Why do you think l returned?

1342
03:01:19,579 --> 03:01:23,920
For a crust of bread, to finish my
life in peace.

1343
03:01:24,590 --> 03:01:28,049
l shall die soon and nothing will
remain after me.

1344
03:01:28,590 --> 03:01:31,170
And l know that l will die soon.

1345
03:01:31,600 --> 03:01:35,059
Nor have you much longer to live.

1346
03:01:36,600 --> 03:01:40,059
Do you want to take your
talent to the grave?

1347
03:01:41,610 --> 03:01:45,069
Why are you silent, Andrei? Give
me at me at least one word.

1348
03:01:45,610 --> 03:01:48,190
lt was l who denounced
that jester then.

1349
03:01:48,610 --> 03:01:51,190
Curse me, but don't stay
silent, Andrei.

1350
03:01:53,620 --> 03:01:55,319
Curse me.

1351
03:04:10,750 --> 03:04:12,450
Well, how is it?

1352
03:04:14,760 --> 03:04:16,459
Come on, then.

1353
03:04:19,760 --> 03:04:21,459
Everyone, get away!

1354
03:04:27,770 --> 03:04:30,350
What's going on up there?

1355
03:04:30,770 --> 03:04:32,469
Everything is okay.

1356
03:04:32,780 --> 03:04:34,479
Come on, come on!
Everyone go up!

1357
03:04:40,780 --> 03:04:41,600
Well? Come on.

1358
03:05:05,809 --> 03:05:08,389
Go on. Give the signal.

1359
03:05:21,760 --> 03:05:23,459
Come on!

1360
03:07:11,799 --> 03:07:16,139
The Grand Prince is coming with
a foreign ambassador.

1361
03:07:16,809 --> 03:07:18,450
ls everything ready?

1362
03:07:19,739 --> 03:07:21,440
lf not, watch out!

1363
03:07:21,750 --> 03:07:23,450
Motherfucker!

1364
03:08:39,760 --> 03:08:44,100
We bless and consecrate this
bell with holy water.

1365
03:08:44,760 --> 03:08:48,219
ln the name of the Father, Son
and Holy Ghost. Amen.

1366
03:09:38,750 --> 03:09:41,329
Look what kind of people are
overseeing here.

1367
03:09:49,760 --> 03:09:51,459
Where are you going?

1368
03:09:58,770 --> 03:10:00,469
lsn't rather peculiar?

1369
03:10:00,770 --> 03:10:03,350
They're all peculiar here.

1370
03:10:15,790 --> 03:10:18,309
Come on, come on, dumbbell!

1371
03:10:34,739 --> 03:10:37,319
Shall l help you, or will you
touch it yourself?

1372
03:11:04,770 --> 03:11:07,350
What do you think will come out
of all this travesty?

1373
03:11:07,770 --> 03:11:09,469
What do you think?

1374
03:11:09,770 --> 03:11:12,350
ln my opinion, nothing good
will come out of this.

1375
03:11:12,780 --> 03:11:15,360
Excuse me, Your Excellency,
but l think you are...

1376
03:11:15,780 --> 03:11:17,479
being deceived by appearances.

1377
03:11:18,719 --> 03:11:20,420
Look at all of this!

1378
03:11:20,719 --> 03:11:24,180
What do you think of this dumb
bell, this awkward scaffold?

1379
03:11:24,719 --> 03:11:27,299
l would sum it up and say this
bell will not ring.

1380
03:11:27,719 --> 03:11:29,420
ln fact, it can't ring.

1381
03:11:29,729 --> 03:11:32,309
Does Your Excellency wish
to make a wager?

1382
03:11:32,729 --> 03:11:34,430
l think you underestimate
the situation these...

1383
03:11:34,729 --> 03:11:36,430
people are in.

1384
03:11:36,729 --> 03:11:39,309
Besides, they were the
ones that built it.

1385
03:11:39,739 --> 03:11:44,079
That may be true, but l wouldn't
venture to call that thing a bell.

1386
03:11:44,739 --> 03:11:47,319
Excellency, they fully
understand...

1387
03:11:47,739 --> 03:11:52,079
That the Prince will behead them
if it doesn't ring.

1388
03:11:52,750 --> 03:11:56,209
Judging from the face
of that youth...

1389
03:11:56,750 --> 03:11:59,329
one could say that he is aware
of the circumstances.

1390
03:11:59,760 --> 03:12:01,459
Don't you think so?

1391
03:12:02,760 --> 03:12:04,459
Excellency...

1392
03:12:04,760 --> 03:12:09,100
Have you heard that the Grand
Prince beheaded his brother?

1393
03:12:09,770 --> 03:12:11,469
lt seems they were twins.

1394
03:12:11,770 --> 03:12:15,229
Look at that marvelous girl!
My God!

1395
03:12:15,770 --> 03:12:19,170
My friend, that girl is not more
than thirteen years old.

1396
03:12:20,709 --> 03:12:23,290
That doesn't make her
Iess attractive.

1397
03:12:23,709 --> 03:12:27,170
Sometimes these girls are
women at the thirteen.

1398
03:12:27,719 --> 03:12:30,299
What's the matter with you,
Your Excellency?

1399
03:15:02,809 --> 03:15:04,510
Come on, come on.

1400
03:15:06,809 --> 03:15:10,270
My father, that old snake, didn't
pass on the secret.

1401
03:15:10,809 --> 03:15:10,270
He died without telling me, he took
it to the grave. Skinflint scoundrel!

1402
03:15:17,790 --> 03:15:19,459
You see, it's turned
out very well.

1403
03:15:19,760 --> 03:15:21,459
Come on, come on.

1404
03:15:22,760 --> 03:15:26,219
Let's go together, you and l.

1405
03:15:27,760 --> 03:15:31,219
You'll cast bells.
l'll paint icons.

1406
03:15:33,770 --> 03:15:36,350
We'll go to the Trinity
Monastery together.

1407
03:15:36,770 --> 03:15:38,469
What a feast day for
the people.

1408
03:15:38,780 --> 03:15:42,239
You've brought them such joy,
and you're crying.

1409
03:15:45,780 --> 03:15:48,360
Come on, come on.

1410
03:16:00,780 --> 03:16:07,360
subtitles - sonicalchemy

